  \cf5 Fail-Fast Philosophy\cf2 : Java encourages catching errors as early as \
  possible. A Session with negative duration should never exist - not \
  even for a millisecond. The constructor should throw \
  IllegalArgumentException immediately. This is fundamentally different \
  from JavaScript's approach where invalid objects often exist and you \
  validate when you use them. \
 \
  \cf5 Exit Codes Matter\cf2 : CLI programs are part of an ecosystem. Shell \
  scripts, CI/CD pipelines, and automation tools all check exit codes to \
  know if operations succeeded. Printing an error but exiting with code 0 \
   tells the shell "success!" - confusing at best, broken automation at \
  worst. \
